          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "D4PI",
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The SuN detector is a 4pi calorimeter",
                "with the shape of a 16 in. x 16 in. barrel with a",
                "1.8-inch-diameter borehole along its axis. The barrel",
                "is segmented into eight optically isolated NaI(Tl)",
                "crystals, each connected to three photomultiplier",
                "tubes (PMTs)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The hydrogen gas-cell target, located in the center",
                "of the SuN detector, was made of plastic with",
                "2-microm-thick molybdenum foils used as entrance and",
                "exit windows. The cell had a length of 4 cm and",
                "included a tantalum ring on the upstream side and",
                "tantalum foil lining the inner walls of the cell, to",
                "shield the plastic from the beam and reduce",
                "beam-induced background. The hydrogen gas inside the",
                "cell was kept at a pressure of ~600 Torr."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 82Kr beam was directed onto a hydrogen gas cell",
                "located at the center of the Summing NaI(Tl) (SuN)",
                "detector. The delivered beam impinged on a hydrogen",
                "gas-cell target and the gamma rays produced by the",
                "reaction were detected by the Summing NaI(Tl) (SuN)",
                "detector. The obtained spectra were analyzed using",
                "the gamma-summing technique and extracted cross",
                "section."
              ]
            }
          ],
